2330.step_text:
Hello and welcome!

[b]I am [color=#e98df7]C.K.[/color] and I am a Wizard![/b]

I will help you to set up your Resoto  installation.

You can always [url=ui_help://You can open this Setup Wizard from the 'Settings' popup in the main menu]come back here later[/url] and use my help to setup different cloud providers.


This setup wizard is shown on start-up until a Collector is configured.

4050.step_text:
Resoto is able to talk to and collect data from different cloud providers.

In order to setup the system, you need to select at least one provider.

After each setuwizard.step_variables["all_count"] = 0p, you will return here.

6270.step_text:
Enter the path to the GCP service account file.

Please make sure that this file is accessible to ResotoWorker.

[b]Example[/b]
[code]/path/to/serviceaccount.json[/code]

6750.step_text:
Have fun and enjoy Resoto!

Join our Discord if you have questions, need support, or want to chat about Infrastructure Intelligence!

6770.step_text:
There was a problem saving your configuration.

Please check if all data you entered is correct!

7433.step_text:
Do you want to scrape your accounts from the organizations?
Scraping the organization requires specific permissions.

Please find additional information in the help at the top right.

11453.step_text: Do you want to finish the setup wizard or go back and change settings?

13529.step_text:
It is possible to scrape different accounts.

Since the organization should not be scraped, do you want to define the list of accounts to scrape?

13714.step_text:
Google Cloud is using service account files in order to connect to an account.
Resoto Worker needs access to such a file to scrape the account.
If you have multiple accounts, you need to provide a service account file for each account.

If Resoto is running inside Google Cloud, it is possible to autodetect the accounts to scrape. In this case permissions need to be set for the instance Resoto is running on.

See help for more information.

32172.step_text:
The AWS Collector is setup.

If you encounter problems while collecting, you can find all the settings in the [url=ui_help://The Configuration Editor can be opened from the main menu or the home screen.]Configuration Editor[/url].

32588.step_text: Do you want to add more GCP service accounts?

32691.step_text:
Please enter the token to access your account.

[url=https://cloud.digitalocean.com/account/api/tokens]Click here[/url] to get help retrieving the access token.

35925.step_text:
Please enter the url of the Kubernetes API server.

This is usually something like:
[code]https://<host>:<port>[/code]
Example: [code]https://k8s-cluster-server.example.com[/code]

36398.headline_text: Finish Setup and Save Config to Core

37287.step_text: My cloud provider is not listed here

37535.step_text:
Resoto will detect the accounts to scrape based on the instance profile Resoto Worker is running on.

You are all set!

42350.step_text: Do you have more cluster tokens to add?

44107.step_text:
We are working hard on expanding our plugins every day.

It could also be that the provider or plugin you want to use is not available here but in other ways of setting up Resoto.

Please check out the docs (click the ? in the upper right corner) and join our Discord to get direct support!

44887.step_text:
The Google Cloud Platform Collector is setup.

If you encounter problems while collecting, you can find all the settings in the [url=ui_help://The Configuration Editor can be opened from the main menu or the home screen.]Configuration Editor[/url].

45237.step_text:
The Kubernetes Collector is setup.

If you encounter problems while collecting, you can find all the settings in the [url=ui_help://The Configuration Editor can be opened from the main menu or the home screen.]Configuration Editor[/url].

48328.step_text:
Please enter the certificate authority data.
This is the base64 encoded certificate authority data of the cluster.

You can find this data in the kubeconfig file in the related cluster section.

Only required in case of a custom certificate.
Leave the field empty, if this is not the case.

49370.step_text: Add additional GCP service account files

49866.step_text:
Do you want Resoto to use a specific role that you have setup in AWS?

This is not required.

53647.step_text:
The DigitalOcean Collector is setup.

If you encounter problems while collecting, you can find all the settings in the [url=ui_help://The Configuration Editor can be opened from the main menu or the home screen.]Configuration Editor[/url].

57110.step_text: Please enter the personal user access token.

61929.step_text: Do you have more cluster configurations to add?

64714.step_text: Use service account file(s) to connect

69475.step_text: Please enter the role name you want to use.

76525.step_text:
AWS allows several access methods to connect to your account(s).

Which one do you want to use?

81056.step_text: Resoto is running on a machine with a configured InstanceProfile

84670.step_text:
Using an instance profile does not require any additional configuration.

Please make sure the permissions are set correctly in IAM for the instance Resoto Worker is running on.

92219.step_text: AWS access environment variables are provided to Resoto

94485.step_text:
Using environment variables does not require any additional configuration.

Please make sure the variables are available to the Resoto Worker process.

97446.step_text: Enter all account ids to be scraped, separated by comma.

97618.step_text:
The simplest way to connect to your cluster is using a kubeconfig file.

For this method to work, Resoto Worker needs to have access to the configured file.

In case this is not possible, or difficult to achieve, you can configure the access directly.

99489.step_text: Use an AWS AccessKey and Secret Key

102181.step_text: Should Resoto assume that role inside the current account as well?

102377.step_text: The Option I would like to use is not listed here

102826.step_text: Resoto has access to a kubeconfig file

107012.step_text: Enter the AWS Access Key ID

109673.step_text:
Resoto can use a kubeconfig file to access your Kubernetes cluster(s).

Please enter the path to the kubeconfig file.

[b]Example[/b]
[code]/path/to/kubeconfig[/code]

114670.step_text: Enter the AWS Secret Access Key

124668.step_text: Do you have more kubeconfig files to access other Kubernetes clusters?

148056.step_text:
Enter the name of your profile.

You can enter multiple profiles separated by a comma.

148682.step_text:
Please enter the name of the cluster.

This name can be chosen freely, but should be unique.

155747.step_text:
I am able to handle the most common cases to connect to AWS.

It looks we do not cover your use case.

Since most options to connect to AWS are implemented, you might be able to configure the access yourself by adjusting the configuration.

Please check out the docs (click the ? in the upper right corner) and join our Discord to get direct support!
